plan_your_pregnancies.description:
Many pregnancies in developing countries are not planned. And with that comes complications, stress and hardship. &#13;
&#13;
A simple mobile app can help women to log their periods and help to calculate their fertile periods so that they can (if possible) try to avoid intercourse during those days or use condoms for that period.

mobile_power.description:
This is a collaborative project of PRAEKELT foundation, Frog design and Nokia siemens and national geographic. The program is called " Project Masiluleke" or Project M. Which means "give wise counsel" or "Lend A Helping Hand". The project M is based in Zulu, south Africa. It aims to use the mobile phone as a communication channel between doctor's visits. The project's intent is to bring those with HIV and TB into the healthcare system earlier, when the diseases can be most effectively treated and/or slowed.&#13;
