accessibility_of_maternal_diagnosis.description:
Because of the baby boom, nowadays the maternity hospitals in China are facing the problem of lacking of resources. The challenge could be how to improve the accessibility of maternal diagnosis in order to help reduce the pressure. For instance, if we could make a routine medical examination available remotely, the hospitals will be able to save lots of resources for many people who need special care.&#13;
&#13;
The picture shows that the pregnant women wait for check-ups at Guangzhou Maternity and Child Health Hospital December 25, 2006 in Guangzhou of Guangdong Province, China. Maternity hospitals have been busier than usual over the past few months as many women try to deliver babies during the pig year of the Chinese lunar calendar. City officials are concerned this baby boom will prompt generational social problems for decades with over-crowding in schools and in the job markets. &#13;
